definitions.definition: An area of land set aside for environment preservation or recreation.

subdefinitions.definition: A tract of ground kept in its natural state, about or adjacent to a residence, such as for the preservation of game, for walking, riding, or the like.
examples: She went to the park for a jog with him.

subdefinitions.definition: A piece of ground in or near a city or town, enclosed and kept for ornament and recreation.
examples: Hyde Park in London;  Central Park in New York

subdefinitions.definition: An enclosed parcel of land stocked with animals for hunting, which one may have by prescription or royal grant.

definitions.definition: A wide, flat-bottomed valley in a mountainous region.
An area used for specific purposes.

subdefinitions.definition: An open space occupied by or reserved for vehicles, matériel or stores.
examples: a wagon park ;   an artillery park

subdefinitions.definition: A partially enclosed basin in which oysters are grown.
An area zoned for a particular (industrial or commercial) purpose.
examples: business park ;  industrial park ;  science park

subdefinitions.definition: An area on which a sporting match is played; ( soccer ) a pitch .

examples: A country's tank park or artillery park .

definitions.definition: A space in which to leave a car ; a parking space .
The gear into which one shifts an automatic transmission when one is parking a car or truck. (Denoted with symbol P on a shifter's labeling.)
examples: If a car seems to be refusing to let you shift out of park , recall that many cars have a safety interlock which requires that your foot must be pressing on the brake pedal before you can shift out of park .

main_definition: An area of land set aside for environment preservation or recreation.
secondary_definitions: ( US ) A wide, flat-bottomed valley in a mountainous region.
An area used for specific purposes.
( Australia , New Zealand , colloquial ) A space in which to leave a car ; a parking space .
( automotive ) The gear into which one shifts an automatic transmission when one is parking a car or truck. (Denoted with symbol P on a shifter's labeling.)
